high and out of control, for those public school systems who cannot control their publicly funded budgets. Guess what? The private/parochial schools that I support through tuition payments manage to control spending, make major improvements in facilities and education and still attract excellent staff and more than enough students who get an excellent, well-balanced and value centered education. You see, every time the local government requests a levy for improvements, I support the increase and voluntary accept the increased taxes because I believe that all persons/children deserve the right to have a good education. But, it seems to be lacking in the public education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="986" language="en" documentId="3920" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="actionjackson1958" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:13PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="33" thumbsDown="0" origId="3920" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="986"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>